description: The ubiquitous convenience store owed its recent revenue drops to inflation, declining cigarette sales and a shift in palates toward fresh food and specialty drinks.
title: 7-Eleven to close over 400 stores in North America

description: Former President Barack Obama bluntly told Black men this week that they need to get over it if they "just aren't feeling the idea of having a woman as president."
title: What the Harris campaign is doing to try to win over more Black men

description: The two-page letter says that Vice President Harris is in excellent health and has “the physical and mental resiliency required to successfully execute the duties of the presidency.”
title: Harris releases medical report, drawing another contrast with Trump

description: NPR's Scott Simon remarks on the legacy of Ethel Kennedy, widow of Robert F. Kennedy. She died Oct. 10 at the age of 96.
title: Opinion: Remembering Ethel Kennedy

description: The Hindu holiday of Navaratri involves some complicated dance moves, passed down from parents to children. But as one mother discovered, the line between passing on cultural traditions and mortifying your teenager daughters can be perilously thin.
title: Passing down tradition on Navaratri

description: In the year since the Hamas-led attacks on Israel, the occupied West Bank has seen an increase in Israeli military raids and attacks by Israeli settlers. More than 600 Palestinians have been killed.
title: The war is in Gaza, but Palestinians in the West Bank are targeted with violence too

description: An effective treatment for opioid addiction is easier to get after the Biden administration changed rules. That's making a difference for some people battling opioid use disorder, but access is still limited.
title: New rules should make methadone easier to get, but change is slow in many places

description: The one-of-a-kind killing of a Kentucky judge, allegedly by the local sheriff, has shaken tight-knit Letcher County, leaving people baffled and unnerved as police try to figure out a motive.
title: Why was a Kentucky judge killed? So far, it remains a mystery

description: A National Geographic team found the boot and foot of whom it suspects to be Andrew "Sandy" Irvine, a 22-year-old climber who went missing on Mount Everest a century ago.
title: National Geographic team may have discovered the foot of a famed Mount Everest climber

description: All the available evidence suggests that a miniscule number of noncitizens vote illegally in federal elections and not in numbers that would sway the outcome of any race.
title: 6 facts about false noncitizen voting claims and the election
